Data Pre Processing













In [17]:



    


#Using mask
#Removing the noises in the image.
#Transfer the  color picutres into the grayscale
#To remove the noise, blur the pictures
#Masking to remove the background. 
#You can see the picures with color and pictures with removing noise and background below.

new_pictures = []
sets = []; getEx = True
for i in pictures:
    blurr = cv2.GaussianBlur(i,(5,5),0)
    hsv = cv2.cvtColor(blurr,cv2.COLOR_BGR2HSV)
    #GREEN PARAMETERS
    lower = (25,40,50)
    upper = (75,255,255)
    mask = cv2.inRange(hsv,lower,upper)
    struc = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE,(11,11))
    mask = cv2.morphologyEx(mask,cv2.MORPH_CLOSE,struc)
    boolean = mask>0
    new = np.zeros_like(i,np.uint8)
    new[boolean] = i[boolean]
    new_pictures.append(new)
    if getEx:
        plt.subplot(2,3,1);plt.imshow(i) # ORIGINAL
        plt.subplot(2,3,2);plt.imshow(blurr) # BLURRED
        plt.subplot(2,3,3);plt.imshow(hsv) # HSV CONVERTED
        plt.subplot(2,3,4);plt.imshow(mask) # MASKED
        plt.subplot(2,3,5);plt.imshow(boolean) # BOOLEAN MASKED
        plt.subplot(2,3,6);plt.imshow(new) # NEW PROCESSED IMAGE
        plt.show()
        getEx = False
new_pictures = np.asarray(new_pictures)
# CLEANED IMAGES
for i in range(8):
    plt.subplot(2,4,i+1)
    plt.imshow(new_pictures[i])

#Using Gaussian Blur to further blur.
def GB(arr):
  for i in range(len(arr)):
    arr[i] = cv2.GaussianBlur(arr[i], (5,5),0)
  return arr

In [37]:



    


# Building the CNN Model with multiple layers.

batch_size = None

model = Sequential()

model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 32, kernel_size = (5,5),padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu', batch_input_shape = (batch_size,256, 256, 3)))


model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 32, kernel_size = (5,5),padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2)))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.2))


model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 64, kernel_size = (3,3),padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 64, kernel_size = (3,3),padding = 'same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=(2,2)))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.3))

model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 128, kernel_size = (3,3),padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(layers.Conv2D(filters = 128, kernel_size = (3,3),padding = 'Same', 
                 activation ='relu'))
model.add(layers.MaxPool2D(pool_size=(2,2), strides=(2,2)))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.4))



model.add(layers.GlobalMaxPooling2D())
model.add(layers.Dense(256, activation = "relu"))
model.add(layers.Dropout(0.5))
model.add(layers.Dense(12, activation = "softmax"))
model.summary()

#Confusion Matrix
plt.subplots(figsize=(40,10)) #plot size 

def make_confusion_matrix(cm, categs,
                          normalize=False,
                          title='Confusion matrix',
                          cmap=plt.cm.RdBu):
    plt.imshow(cm, interpolation='nearest', cmap=cmap)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.colorbar()
    tick_marks = np.arange(len(categs))
    plt.xticks(tick_marks, categs, rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(tick_marks, categs)

    if normalize:
        cm = cm.astype('float') / cm.sum(axis=1)[:, np.newaxis]

    thresh = cm.max() / 2.
    for i, j in itertools.product(range(cm.shape[0]), range(cm.shape[1])):
        plt.text(j, i, cm[i, j],
                 horizontalalignment="center",
                 color="white" if cm[i, j] > thresh else "black")

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.ylabel('True Category')
    plt.xlabel('Predicted Category')

# Predicting validation dataset
Y_pred = model.predict(X_val)
# Transfer predictions categs to one hot vectors 
Y_pred_categs = np.argmax(Y_pred,axis = 1) 
# Transfer validation observations to one hot vectors
Y_true = np.argmax(Y_val,axis = 1) 
# plotting the confusion matrix
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(Y_true, Y_pred_categs) 
# plot the confusion matrix
make_confusion_matrix(conf_matrix, categs = range(12))
